STICKY CHICKEN RICE BOWL

This can be enjoyed hot or cold which is perfect if you want to meal prep it for work or school and don’t have access to a microwave 💃🏻
-Chicken breast, cooked weight (100g)
-Sushi rice/ short grain rice, cooked weight (150g)
-Cucumber, diced 

Sauce:
-Natural peanut butter, (10g) @ohmega_nutbutters 
-Dark soy sauce, (5g) *
-1/2 -1 tsp chilli flakes, to your taste
-1 tbsp water

Garnish:
-Sesame seeds, 1g
-Spring onion 

1.) Prepare your sushi rice
2.) Pan fry the chicken with your desired seasoning (I used paprika) until cooked through and then slice into pieces
3.) Combine the sauce in a small bowl, add the chicken and evenly coat it in sauce
4.) Add everything to a bowl, garnish and enjoy! 

*I used thick dark soy sauce for this, if you use a regular thin soy sauce you may need to add a little more and leave out the water

439 calories
37.5g protein
45.6g carbs
10.4g fat

node.text:
Simple principles that will enable you to lose weight.
Follow @health_challlenge
By @oli.Rogers
-
As with any weight loss/fat loss goal, a calorie deficit is by far the number 1 most important factor in determining weight loss.
Additionally avoiding liquid calories, such as sodas, alcohol, (unnecessary additional/wasted calories.)
Fill up on veggies, and
eating protein at every meal, are all staple habit changes if you are looking to drop body fat.
-
A full night's sleep, consistent exercise (3x per week minimum), and increased activity like upping your step count will also assist your fat loss goals.
-
An often overlooked aspect regarding fat loss is enjoyment. You've got to somewhat enjoy the process. If you dread every aspect of the journey, you will be more likely to burn out and give up.
-
If you added a Rule, what would yours be?
👥 tag a friend!
.

KRAPFEN DOUGNUT BAKED OATS 🥵 • EXPLOSIVE 💣 •

Last  morning I was running by a local bakery and I saw some Krapfen. First thing that came to my mind was "I want it now!", but I had no money with me. So I thought, "Well, I will go home and make it my own way. Now!"

You HAVE to try this!

SAVE FOR THE BOMB‼️

dEats🌱
- 1/2 banana
- 50g (1/2 cup) oat flour
- 8–15g (1 tbsp) maple syrup
- 10g (1 tbsp) cashew or nut butter 
- 1/2 tsp baking powder
- 1/3 tsp vanilla extract
- 100/110ml (1/2 cup) nondairy milk
- 70g (1/3 cup) protein vanilla dessert (or vanilla pudding)
- Sprinkle powdered sugar 
Directions⏱ 
- Heat oven to 180 Cº (360 Fº).
- In a bowl mash 1/2 banana and combine with oat flour, maple syrup, cashew butter, vanilla extract and baking powder. Add the nondairy milk and stir.
- Transfer to an ovenproof bowl 3/4 batter and fill with the vanilla protein dessert in the center. Cover with the remaining batter.
- Bake for 20 – 25 minutes.
- Sprinkle with some powdered sugar.
.
.
.

Coconut Panko Crusted Tofu with Mango Avocado Salad and Coconut Lime Rice by @plantbased.traveler ❤️

Crispy tofu pieces, creamy avocado, sweet mango, a hint of spice, lots of lime and coconut flavours….yes please! 😋

Tofu:
1 block extra firm tofu, lightly pressed
1/4 cup coconut or other plant milk 
2 tbsp cornstarch 
Salt
1/2 cup unsweetened coconut flakes 
1/2 cup panko bread crumbs
1-2 tbsp coconut oil 

Mango Avocado Salad:
1 mango
1 avocado 
1 small red onion
1 jalapeño (seeded for less heat) 
Juice of 1 large lime
Salt to taste 
A handful of chopped cilantro 

Instructions: 
Finely dice red onion and jalapeño, add both to a bowl, and sprinkle with salt and lime juice. 
In a shallow bowl, whisk together cornstarch and coconut milk, and to a second bowl add breadcrumbs and coconut flakes. If the coconut flakes are very large, I recommend pulsing them in a food processor until smaller in size. 
Cut tofu in half, each half into slices, and pat slices dry with a clean kitchen or paper towel. 
Season from both sides with salt. 
Add each slice to the cornstarch mix, then press them into the coconut breadcrumbs until coated from all sides.
Heat up coconut oil in a large (cast iron) skillet, and fry tofu from both sides for about 3 minutes or until golden. 
Peel mango and avocado, cut them into medium sized pieces, and add to the red onion jalapeño mix together with the chopped cilantro. 
Serve tofu and mango avocado salad over some rice, and enjoy! 

Tip: Toss any leftover coconut panko mix in the hot pan until golden, and serve it as a crunchy topping! 

For the rice, I simply cook white, rinsed rice with salt and coconut water (instead of regular water), then add lemon zest and lemon juice at the end.
